11:01.426 --> 11:03.427
Would you like
some white wine?

11:03.428 --> 11:04.595
Yes, please.

11:04.596 --> 11:06.330
I'll give you a hand.
Sure.

11:06.331 --> 11:09.267
This is a very interesting
house, wilson.

11:09.268 --> 11:11.636
Or should I
call you "wilson"?

11:13.538 --> 11:16.006
Judith, in addition
to being my professor,

11:16.007 --> 11:18.942
Mentor, friend, is also
a renowned author.

11:18.943 --> 11:22.045
Oh, hardly renowned.
My book sold about
four copies.

11:22.046 --> 11:24.548
Two of which were
to my children.

11:24.549 --> 11:26.216
I wrote a book once.

11:26.217 --> 11:29.086
<i>How to maintain</i>
<i>your bench grinder.</i>

11:30.255 --> 11:32.623
That sold no copies.

11:32.624 --> 11:34.592
Well, it was probably more
exciting than my book.

11:34.593 --> 11:38.696
It was called
<i>the psychophysiological indices</i>
<i>of amorous connections...</i>

11:38.697 --> 11:41.599
<i>Among termites</i>
<i>of the southwest.</i>

11:41.600 --> 11:43.668
How did you know that?

11:43.669 --> 11:47.938
Because I have read it.
It is wonderful!

11:47.939 --> 11:49.640
I mean, it's practically
the bible

11:49.641 --> 11:52.376
For anyone interested in
the mating pattern of insects.

11:52.377 --> 11:54.978
All two of you.

11:57.516 --> 11:59.249
You see,
I am quite the devotee

11:59.250 --> 12:02.252
Of what I humorously term
"insexuality."

12:02.253 --> 12:04.455
<i>(judith laughs)</i>

12:04.456 --> 12:06.424
I can't believe
you actually read my book.

12:06.425 --> 12:08.258
I've got it right here.
I'll show you.

12:08.259 --> 12:10.361
We'll have to talk
some insects over dinner.

12:10.362 --> 12:14.932
Yeah. 'cause usually
over here we eat
insects for dinner.

12:14.933 --> 12:16.767
<i>(wilson)</i> here it is.

12:19.671 --> 12:21.539
