is intellectualize

15:13.812 --> 15:15.513
Or say something weird.

15:15.514 --> 15:17.180
He always says
something weird.

15:17.181 --> 15:20.317
That's what makes
wilson wilson wilson.

15:25.123 --> 15:26.991
I think you should
talk to him.
No, I'm not -

15:26.992 --> 15:28.759
You're the only one
that's got a chance
of getting through to him.

15:28.760 --> 15:32.796
I'm supposed to go
talk to that man about
emotions and intimacy?

15:32.797 --> 15:35.032
Granted, you're not
the obvious choice.

15:35.033 --> 15:37.401
But desperate times call
for desperate measures.

15:37.402 --> 15:39.803
If he doesn't
open up to her,
he is gonna lose her.

15:43.642 --> 15:47.945
<i>(grunting)</i> ok, moving
to the next level.

15:47.946 --> 15:49.112
Wilson, you home?

15:49.113 --> 15:51.214
I'm in the kitchen, tim,
making my haggis.

15:51.215 --> 15:52.650
Hey. <i>(sniffs)</i>

15:52.651 --> 15:55.285
You know, that stuff
doesn't smell half-bad.

15:55.286 --> 15:57.287
Pretty excited about having
judith over for dinner?

15:57.288 --> 15:58.622
Oh, yes, indeed.

15:58.623 --> 16:00.591
You really like her?
Oh, yes.

16:00.592 --> 16:03.393
Oh, no. Oh.

16:03.394 --> 16:05.395
Tim, is there something
you want to tell me?

16:05.396 --> 16:08.065
No, there's something
jill wants me to tell you.

16:08.066 --> 16:09.533
Uh...

16:09.534 --> 16:11.569
Judith is having a problem.

16:11.570 --> 16:13.537
What kind of a problem?
Is she all right?

16:13.538 --> 16:15.405
Oh, she's fine.

16:15.406 --> 16:18.909
The problem is with you.

16:18.910 --> 16:21.845
I don't understand.
Things were going so well.

16:21.846 --> 16:24.081
We even made plans to go
to the megalesia festival

16:24.082 --> 16:27.384
To commemorate
the end of the punic war.

16:29.588 --> 16:32.422
She... She says
that - that ...

16:32.423 --> 16:34.458
She told jill that
she doesn't even
think she knows you.

16:34.459 --> 16:36.927
That every time she tries
to get you to open up

16:36.928 --> 16:38.596
You just say something
intellectual.

16:38.597 --> 16:41.699
Oh, my, my, my.
I must be displaying
the symptomatic behavior

16:41.700 --> 16:44.167
Of the classic male
emotional distancer,

16:44.168 --> 16:46.971
Precipitating her
to overfunction
in the relationship,

16:46.972 --> 16:49.773
Therefore causing
deep-seated resentment.

16:49.774 --> 16:52.509
So knock it off.

16:52.510 --> 16:56.313
Tim, I don't take easily
to personal or emotional
revelation.

16:56.314 --> 16:58.115
No guy does.
Opening up emotionally

16:58.116 --> 17:01.685
Is just a horrible thing
women make us do.

17:01.686 --> 17:04.922
Well, tim, I'm just not sure
that I can do that.

17:12.797 --> 17:14.498
Yes, you can.

17:14.499 --> 17:16.266
Just use
the word "feel" more.

17:16.267 --> 17:19.803
You know, like,
"I feel hungry."
"I feel tired."

17:19.804 --> 17:22.940
"I feel big." "I feel small."
"I feel bloated."

17:22.941 --> 17:26.510
Tim, I think that judith
and I weren't meant to be.

17:26.511 --> 17:30.014
To be or not to be,
that is not the question.

17:31.382 --> 17:33.884
You've got to learn
how to open up to this woman,

17:33.885 --> 17:35.753
Otherwise you're gonna be
all by yourself

17:35.754 --> 17:38.055
At that milk of magnesia
festival.

17:42.727 --> 17:45.428
So, are you enjoying
your haggis?

17:45.429 --> 17:48.465
It's very tender.
What's in this?

17:48.466 --> 17:51.601
That is sheep's liver
and other assorted organs.

17:51.602 --> 17:53.570
It's very filling.

17:55.406 --> 17:56.974
These are lovely candles.

17:56.975 --> 17:59.109
Mm.

17:59.110 --> 18:01.444
Well, thank you.

18:01.445 --> 18:04.514
You know, I've always
found it fascinating
how a candle burns.

18:04.515 --> 18:07.551
The hot flame moves downward,
thus melting the wax,

18:07.552 --> 18:10.854
Which rises through the wick
through capillary action...

18:12.557 --> 18:14.457
Oh, boy, that was dull.

18:16.127 --> 18:19.897
Wilson, I think
we should talk.

18:19.898 --> 18:21.732
I know what you're
gonna say, judith.

18:21.733 --> 18:23.533
I haven't been
very open to you.

18:23.534 --> 18:26.770
I don't understand why a man
who can talk brilliantly
about anything

18:26.771 --> 18:29.406
Can't tell me about the one
thing I really want to know.

18:30.942 --> 18:35.045
Well, my family never
really talked much
about personal matters.

18:35.046 --> 18:39.349
Especially my father,
wilson wilson sr.

18:41.319 --> 18:43.687
What was he like?

18:43.688 --> 18:45.589
He was a scientist

18:45.590 --> 18:48.658
Who didn't put too much
stock in emotions.

18:48.659 --> 18:51.428
Must have been very
difficult to grow up
with a man like that.

18:51.429 --> 18:53.630
Mm. It was.

18:53.631 --> 18:56.299
You know,
I loved my father.

18:56.300 --> 19:00.503
It always hurt me when
he kept me at a distance.

19:00.504 --> 19:03.640
And the last thing
I ever wanted was
to be like him.

19:03.641 --> 19:05.375
But you're not.

19:05.376 --> 19:08.045
You believe that
feelings matter.

19:09.580 --> 19:13.150
I know that, because I see
the way you care about mine.

19:18.389 --> 19:21.658
You know, judith...

19:21.659 --> 19:26.897
I've never been
open with a woman
since my wife died.

19:26.898 --> 19:29.666
But I would really like
to try with you.

19:29.667 --> 19:31.769
I'd like that too.

19:36.908 --> 19:38.909
Well, maybe we can
talk about it tomorrow

19:38.910 --> 19:41.111
At the megalesia festival.

19:41.112 --> 19:43.814
If you still want to go.

19:43.815 --> 19:48.418
I wouldn't want to celebrate
the end of the punic war
with anyone else.

19:48.419 --> 19:52.455
Even though I have
absolutely no idea
what the punic war was.

19:52.456 --> 19:54.091
Well, actually,
it's fascinating.

19:54.092 --> 19:56.927
It was when rome
saved itself by...

19:56.928 --> 19:59.629
Oh, who the hell cares?
They'll have beer.

20:04.836 --> 20:08.205
You know, judith,
not to bore you
with more facts...

20:13.444 --> 20:15.112
...But primitive man believed

20:15.113 --> 20:18.481
That the air he breathed
had magic powers.

20:18.482 --> 20:20.750
I'm not bored.

20:20.751 --> 20:25.289
And when a man
and a woman kissed,

20:25.290 --> 20:28.425
It was as if their souls
were mingling.

21:00.691 --> 21:02.192
Oh, look, mark.

21:02.193 --> 21:04.761
It's the sister
we've always wanted.

21:06.130 --> 21:08.765
Hello, bradina.

21:08.766 --> 21:10.767
Laugh all you want.

21:10.768 --> 21:12.402
But I've been going out
with jessica for two weeks,

21:12.403 --> 21:14.938
And she hasn't
noticed one zit.

21:14.939 --> 21:19.276
Yeah, but that doesn't
explain the lipstick
and the mascara.

21:20.879 --> 21:22.880
Well, I dumped out
all mom's makeup.

21:22.881 --> 21:24.714
Which do you think
covers my zits better?

21:24.715 --> 21:27.617
Bashful beige
or nearly nude?

21:28.953 --> 21:31.054
This is too weird.

21:31.055 --> 21:33.323
<i>(doorbell)</i>
I got it!

21:35.226 --> 21:36.860
Hi. Is brad here?

21:36.861 --> 21:39.729
Yeah. He's in the kitchen,
putting on his makeup.

21:46.337 --> 21:48.005
Hey, brad.

21:51.709 --> 21:55.645
Hey, jessica!
What are you doing here?

21:55.646 --> 21:57.314
I, um...

21:57.315 --> 21:59.649
I just thought
maybe we could go
to practice together.

21:59.650 --> 22:01.218
Well, um...

22:01.219 --> 22:05.055
Brad, are you trying
to cover up that zit
on your chin?

22:07.392 --> 22:10.994
Oh, man. I knew I should
have gone with bashful beige.

22:14.498 --> 22:19.937
No. No, I think
that bashful beige
is too dark for you.

22:19.938 --> 22:22.973
You'd look better
in posy pink.

22:22.974 --> 22:25.675
I think I have that.

22:29.513 --> 22:31.014
All right. Now, guys,
you need to remember

22:31.015 --> 22:33.917
To apply it gently
and blend thoroughly,

22:33.918 --> 22:35.452
Because you always want

22:35.453 --> 22:38.388
That natural
boy-next-door look.

22:42.160 --> 22:46.930
There you go. Good job.
